Root cause investigation revealed Kennametal India's
/company/KENNAMET/consolidated/ page is FROZEN at Sep 2022 because the
company stopped publishing consolidated quarterly results after that
date. Their /company/KENNAMET/ (standalone) page has continued through
Mar 2026.

My previous staleness retry only tried the search API, which returned
the same /company/KENNAMET/ slug — and then I appended /consolidated/
again, getting back the same frozen page. Standalone variant was
never tested.

Three-tier retry chain now:

1. Initial fetch: /company/{symbol}/consolidated/ (existing default)

2. STANDALONE RETRY (NEW): if the quarters section's latest data-date-key
   year is 1+ years behind current year, immediately try
   /company/{symbol}/ standalone. Companies like KENNAMET that switched
   from consolidated to standalone reporting fall through here.

3. SEARCH API RETRY (existing, improved): if both consolidated and
   standalone are stale, try the search API. Tests up to 3 candidate
   companies, each with both consolidated and standalone variants.
   Picks whichever returns the highest year.

Also tightened the staleness detector to look ONLY inside the
<section id="quarters"> block, using data-date-key="YYYY-MM-DD"
attributes which Screener emits on every quarter <th>. The previous
regex matched any 'Mar/Jun/Sep/Dec YYYY' anywhere in the HTML, which
could falsely report freshness based on annual P&L row labels.

After deploy, KENNAMET should auto-resolve to standalone and show
Mar 2026 data: Revenue ₹403 Cr, EBITDA ₹77 Cr, PAT ₹51 Cr. The red
staleness banner won't fire because the standalone retry succeeds.

